Jadabs
------

see for more information http://wlab.ethz.ch/jadabs
copyright by ETH, Andreas Frei

Minimal
--------
With the minimal version you can start a peer like the following:

linux> ./runpeer.sh
win> runpeer.bat

To start a second peer make a copy of this folder and change inside
the runpeer -Dch.ethz.jadabs.jxme.peeralias=$HOSTNAME the HOSTNAME to an
other name, e.g. peer2.



Full
----
Contains all our libraries together with the ones from Knopflerfish (KF).
You can start with KF-GUI or with a very simple RemoteBundle Admin tool.

KF-GUI:

linux> ./runpeer.sh init-kf
win> runpeer.bat init-kf

RemoteBundle-Admin GUI

linux> ./runpeer.sh init-gui-linux
win> runpeer.bat init-gui-win



Full-Prose
----------
All the above scripts can also be run by adding prose as a parameter.
Currently this works only for Linux.

linux> ./runpeer.sh init prose
linux> ./runpeer.sh init-kf prose
linux> ./runpeer.sh init-gui-linux prose 
